          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-10-15 11:42:24" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to begin an association with someone, whether temporary or permanent{N:001}</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to join</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to join oneself to</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to become a part of</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Though the Greek text of {S:04400802900018} says literally ‘join this carriage,’ in reality, of course, the association is not directly with the carriage, but with the man riding in the carriage. It is therefore necessary in a number of languages to translate κολλήθητι τῷ ἅρματι τούτῳ as ‘join the man riding in this carriage.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
